00:30:51.318 --> 00:30:54.598
prevent a lot of those late effects from occurring by

531
00:30:55.278 --> 00:30:59.058
primary prevention. So I think that that really, to me, is where we

532
00:30:59.098 --> 00:31:02.938
should shift the paradigm and focus from the direction of research in this

533
00:31:02.958 --> 00:31:03.718
population.

534
00:31:04.618 --> 00:31:08.478
So for the rest of this presentation, the way I want to kind of make sure that

535
00:31:08.778 --> 00:31:12.338
I make my case is just to really give you a little bit of background of genetics

536
00:31:12.378 --> 00:31:15.578
and survivorship, and for that, I'm going to focus on cardiomyopathy.

537
00:31:16.158 --> 00:31:17.478
Cardiovascular outcomes in

538
00:31:18.618 --> 00:31:22.068
the chronic health condition realm is the number one morbidity and mortality,

539
00:31:22.118 --> 00:31:23.198
importantly mortality,

540
00:31:24.278 --> 00:31:27.158
that our patients face. So I think that that's helpful to have a better

541
00:31:27.178 --> 00:31:30.338
understanding of that. And then this is where I'm going to shift to being an

542
00:31:30.378 --> 00:31:34.358
endocrinologist and really try to persuade the oncologists in this

543
00:31:34.378 --> 00:31:36.048
audience to care about

