00:32:28.798 --> 00:32:30.838
achieve is the five-year overall survival,

561
00:32:31.758 --> 00:32:34.608
but survival is not equivalent to survivorship.

562
00:32:35.138 --> 00:32:39.078
I think that that's an important concept to recognize, because surviving

563
00:32:39.118 --> 00:32:41.898
your cancer alone does not mean that you actually have full

564
00:32:41.938 --> 00:32:45.928
recovery. So we do know, especially as you care for these patients, there's

565
00:32:45.978 --> 00:32:49.868
a heterogeneity in outcomes. And currently, the way our system is

566
00:32:49.878 --> 00:32:52.668
set up, we really have some gaps in care.

567
00:32:53.118 --> 00:32:55.018
What we do is a lot of reactive care.

568
00:32:55.098 --> 00:32:59.038
You just basically do organ-based screening, and once you find an abnormality, then

569
00:32:59.078 --> 00:33:02.718
you address that. Our care guidelines are very

570
00:33:02.758 --> 00:33:04.638
