571
00:33:04.678 --> 00:33:08.498
They're not patient-centered, so they're not really personalized.

572
00:33:08.538 --> 00:33:12.318
And so despite these being some obstacles, I think it actually presents wonderful

573
00:33:12.378 --> 00:33:16.098
opportunities for us to actually look at these as ways to

574
00:33:16.158 --> 00:33:19.118
integrate more longitudinal clinical data.

575
00:33:19.958 --> 00:33:23.498
I think this is where it's important to have structured data elements across

576
00:33:23.558 --> 00:33:27.298
institutions where we can really harmonize and bring the data together,

577
00:33:27.778 --> 00:33:31.338
and really an opportunity for us to kind of incorporate molecular and genomic

578
00:33:31.398 --> 00:33:35.258
profiling for real-world evidence to give us an approach for

579
00:33:35.278 --> 00:33:39.258
risk stratified precision survivorship care.

580
00:33:39.278 --> 00:33:43.138
So I think to just start off with cardiomyopathy, again, as the oncologists in

581
00:33:43.178 --> 00:33:44.458
this audience, I don't need to

582
00:33:45.658 --> 00:33:49.648
remind you that anthracycline chemotherapy is a risk factor for cardiomyopathy,

583
00:33:49.778 --> 00:33:51.458
but there are other risk modifiers.

584
00:33:51.498 --> 00:33:51.698
So

585
00:33:52.578 --> 00:33:56.398
whether the patient receives chest radiation, the young age at the time of cancer

586
00:33:56.438 --> 00:33:59.898
diagnosis, female sex, other comorbidities like

587
00:33:59.918 --> 00:34:03.568
hypertension, obesity, those can really impact this outcome.

588
00:34:03.898 --> 00:34:07.758
And as you can see that there's a direct dose response relationship

589
00:34:07.778 --> 00:34:11.569
between anthracyclines and the risk of cardiomyopathy, and that risk really

590
00:34:11.598 --> 00:34:14.919
starts declaring itself once you receive about 100 to

591
00:34:14.978 --> 00:34:17.578
150 milligrams per meter squared of

592
00:34:17.638 --> 00:34:21.478
anthracyclines. And the mechanism in general is just

593
00:34:21.498 --> 00:34:24.078
polygenic. It's also multiple mechanisms.

594
00:34:24.118 --> 00:34:27.158
It's not just one mechanism that leads to the

595
00:34:27.218 --> 00:34:30.828
anthracycline-mediated cardiomyopathy, and some of the mechanisms are just sort of

596
00:34:31.118 --> 00:34:34.879
outlined on this figure here. And so whether it's from reactive oxygen

597
00:34:34.998 --> 00:34:38.638
species production, DNA damage, the impact of

598
00:34:38.658 --> 00:34:41.899
doxorubicin transports the metabolism of that drug,

599
00:34:42.118 --> 00:34:44.498
interference with iron uptake, and/or

600
00:34:46.598 --> 00:34:49.518
calcium handling, where you have accumulation of calcium

601
00:34:49.819 --> 00:34:51.778
intracellularly and damage of sarcomere.

602
00:34:51.839 --> 00:34:52.558
So those are all

603
00:34:53.678 --> 00:34:56.819
mechanisms that kind of lend together to lead to

604
00:34:56.859 --> 00:34:58.938
anthracycline-mediated cardiomyopathy.

605
00:34:59.678 --> 00:35:03.497
So I think for this purposes of this brief presentation, what I'm going to

606
00:35:03.558 --> 00:35:07.497
give you is just some snippets, how does some of these genes kind

607
00:35:07.538 --> 00:35:11.238
of play into the different components of

